<div class="text-center">

<h2>Welcome to ☕️ 418-Bot!</h2>

  <% if current_user.nil? %>
    <a href="https://slack.com/oauth/authorize?scope=identity.basic,identity.team&client_id=107333465906.108008566694"><img alt="Sign in with Slack" height="40" width="172" src="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/sign_in_with_slack.png" srcset="https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/sign_in_with_slack.png 1x, https://platform.slack-edge.com/img/sign_in_with_slack@2x.png 2x" /></a>
  <% else %>
    <%= link_to "Logout", logout_path, method: :destroy %>
  <% end %>

  <% flash.each do |key, value| %>
    <%= content_tag :div, value, class: "flash #{key}" %>
  <% end %>

  <h5>
    <%= @display %>
  </h5>

  <p>
    List of 418-Bot commands:
    <table class="col-7 centered table table-striped table-hover main-page-table">
      <thead>
          <tr>
              <th class="command-column">command</th>
              <th>result</th>
              <th>extra</th>
          </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
          <tr>
              <td class="command-column">/coffee_brewing</td>
              <td>creates a record of coffee being brewed (default location is your Slack team name)</td>
              <td>You can also use '/coffee_brewing Blake' to add a custom location (in this case, Blake) and/or '/coffee_brewing Blake and it's delicious!' to add a description.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
              <td class="command-column">/coffee_brewing #how</td>
              <td>returns a quick guide to brewing a great pot of coffee</td>
              <td>You can also click <a href="/how_to_brew" class="link-decoration">here</a> for location specific info.</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
              <td class="command-column">/coffee_brewing #out</td>
              <td>returns instructions for what to do when we're out of coffee</td>
              <td>More on this coming soon...</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
              <td class="command-column">/last_brewed</td>
              <td>returns the last location and time coffee was brewed</td>
              <td>You can use /last_brewed followed by a number to retrieve more brew records (useful if the last brew wasn't at your location!).</td>
          </tr>
      </tbody>
  </table>
  </p>
  <p>
    Any questions? Email <a href="mailto:noah@noahberman.org">noah at noahberman dot org</a>! hope you enjoy :)
  </p>

</div>
